3/14/20, 9:55 PM - Mina: For the strawman fallacy, when. The argument is raised , the arguer takes only a portion of the argument and centers on it . When it's a broader topic. But the red herring no.  The arguer totally digresses from the topic.
3/14/20, 9:55 PM - Mina: Example
3/14/20, 9:56 PM - Mina: Kennedy agyapong who is not an economist will meet economists on a show and when. 3/27/20, 11:49 PM - Success: Summary of the Restrictions Imposed on Selected Areas in Ghana by Government for 2weeks.

1.President Akufo-Addo has announced that effective Monday, 30th March, 2020 at 1 am under the Imposition of Restrictions Act, 2020 (Act 1012), there will be restrictions on movement of persons in the Greater Accra Metropolitan Area (GAMA, which include Awutu Senya East ), and the Greater Kumasi Metropolitan Area and contiguous districts, for a period of two (2) weeks or 14 days  subject to review. 

2.In Greater Accra, the following areas will be affected:
- Accra Metropolis
-Tema Metropolis
-Tema West 
-Kpone Katamanso
-Krowor 
-Ledzokuku 
-Adentan 
- Ashiaman 
La-Nkwantanang-Madina
-La-Dade-Kotopon
-Okaikwei North 
-Ablekuma North
-Ablekuma West
-Ablekuma Central
-Ayawaso East
-Ayawaso North
-Ayawaso West 
-Ayawaso Central
-Ga North
-Ga West
-Ga South 
-Ga Central
Ga East
-Korle-Klottey 
-Weija/Gbawe
-Awutu Senya East
 
3.In the Greater Kumasi Metropolitan Area  the following areas are affected:
*Kumasi Metropolis; 
*Asokwa
* Suame
*Old Tafo 
*Oforikrom 
*Asokore Mampong 
*Kwadaso 
*Atwima Nwabiagya 
*Kwabre East
*Ejisu
*Afigya-Kwabre South 
*Bosomtwe 
*Atwima Kwanwoma 
*Atwima Nwabiagya North   

4.This means that everyone resident in these areas must stay at home for the next two weeks or 14 days,  However, if you must go out, it must only be to get essential items such as food, water, medicine, undertake banking transactions, or to use public toilet facilities. But, as much as possible, stay at, h.ome.

5.There shal l be, during this period, no inter-city movement of vehicles and aircraft for private or commercial purposes for the areas of the restrictive measures, except for vehicles and aircrafts providing essential services and those carrying cargo. 

6.-Riders of motorbikes are not allowed to carry any additional person, and all intra-city passenger vehicles, such as trotros and taxis, must reduce the number of passengers in order to observe appropriate social distancing and hygiene protocols. 

7. All commercial vehicle stations shall observe appropriate hygiene protocols and social distancing.

8.Individuals and institutions providing the following services shall be exempted from the restrictions:
-Members of the Executive, Legislature and the Judiciary;
-Production, distribution and marketing of food, beverages, pharmaceuticals, medicine, paper and plastic packages.
-Environmental and sanitation activities;
-VALCO staff
-Road and Railway
construction workers; 
-Mining workers;
-Fisherfolk;
-Members of the security agencies assigned lawful duties;
-The staff of electricity, water, telecommunications, e-commerce and digital service providers; and
-Fuel stations staff.

5/1/20, 5:50 AM - Mina: In the quest of(parasites) organisms which live in or on the body of other organisms, obtain nourishment and finally cause harm to the second organisms(hosts), they face certain challenges . These challenges are considered the inhibitors of the expressionof the full potential of parasites.  Given that parasites interact at close range with the hosts, hosts deploy mechanisms such as immune suppression or attacks or behaviorally choosing a site to live or being active at certain times of the day and season to avoid parasites. Both the parasitesand hosts play rital roles in their environment to ensure their continuous survival. Let elaborate four challenges parasites face in their quest to inhabit a biotic environment. First suppression or attacks by the host's immune system, then difficulty in obtaining the required nourishment due to less developed digestive system, inability of parasites to complete their their life cycle and variation in matching of host and parasite genomes.  


Most living species are parasitic. Hosts in turn deploy their immune systems to prevent infections or keep the parasites in check . The immune systemis one of the most complex systems and shows many signs of coevolution with parasites . The immune system is well tuned to it's task , as long lived multicellular organisms would probably not be able to survive and outpace their short-lived and numerous parasites. Nonetheless, immune responses vary among host's life cycle or infection by different parasite types. For instance, a host may be killed before the full potential of transmission will be exploited.

Again, most parasites due to their less elaborate digestive systems, lack adequate nourishment from the host organism. This food aquisition is by permeable tegument for active absorption and possesses muscular pharynx. These parasites due to this, depend on predigested food from host. Where in the absence of host nutrition, parasites cannot obtain nourishment from other sources. 

Parasites are faced with the challenge of variationin host and parasite genomes. In that only some parasite genotypes are able to infect a particular host genotype, and vice versa,only some host genotypes are able to resist a particular set of parasite genotypes. This means that not all parasites can infect all hosts and not all hosts can resist all parasites. Some hosts have mechanisms to counter the effect of some parasites and some parasites have mechanisms to outpace the resistance of hosts.

Finally, inability of parasites to complete their life cycle due to the heteroxenous nature of development affects their continuous survival. Some parasites require more than one host to complete it's lifecycle, hence if the host is killed whilst containing the parasites, then the life cycle will not be complete since it requires a definitive host to complete it's life cycle. For example, the life cycle of taenia solium begins from an infected human, to pigs to pig's intestinesand then back to humans. Here if the pig gets killed the parasite wouldn't achieve it's full potential on the host by it's inability to complete it's life cycle.
